sible location for our attendees.</p>\\n\\n        <h3>Map</h3>\\n        <div class=\\\"map-container\\\">\\n            <!-- Replace with the actual Google Maps embed code for the conference venue -->\\n            <iframe src=\\\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d12624.429458279037!2d-122.4194!3d37.7749!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8085808933d686b1%3A0xe984e94f2683c119!2sSan%20Francisco%2C%20CA%2C%20USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1702842473944!5m2!1sen!2sus\\\" width=\\\"600\\\" height=\\\"450\\\" style=\\\"border:0;\\\" allowfullscreen=\\\"\\\" loading=\\\"lazy\\\"></iframe>\\n        </div>\\n    </div>\\n</section>\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n1. The venue address should be fully specified rather than stating it will be announced later.\\n2. Include a concrete location name and street address (e.g., Moscone Center, 747 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA).\\n3. Update the map iframe to point directly at that address.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```html\\n<section id=\\\"venue\\\">\\n    <div class=\\\"container\\\">\\n        <h2>Venue</h2>\\n        <p>The International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR) 2025 will be held at:</p>\\n        <address>\\n            Moscone Center<br>\\n            747 Howard St<br>\\n            San Francisco, CA 94103<br>\\n            United States\\n        </address>\\n        \\n        <h3>Conference Location</h3>\\n        <p>The Moscone Center is located in the heart of downtown San Francisco, within walking distance of major hotels, public transit, and local landmarks.</p>\\n\\n        <h3>Map</h3>\\n        <div class=\\\"map-container\\\">\\n            <iframe\\n                src=\\\"https://www.google.com/maps?q=Moscone+Center,+747+Howard+St,+San+Francisco,+CA+94103,+USA&output=embed\\\"\\n                width=\\\"600\\\"\\n                height=\\\"450\\\"\\n                style=\\\"border:0;\\\"\\n                allowfullscreen=\\\"\\\"\\n                loading=\\\"lazy\\\">\\n            </iframe>\\n        </div>\\n    </div>\\n</section>\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nI want to create a website for the following conference:\\n    1). Conference Name: International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR2025)  \\n    2). Date: April 27, 2025 to May 1, 2025  \\n    3). Location: San Francisco, California, United States\\n    4). Organizer: International Association for Learning Representations\\n    Please generate a detailed website structure and content for this conference. \\n    For each section, provide example HTML content. \\n    Additionally, create a sample CSS stylesheet to style the website. \\n    Ensure the content is professional, clear, and suitable for an international academic conference.\\n    Note that:\\n    1). The previous information I gave you must be included.\\n    2). The website should have conference schedule part.\\n    3). The website should have conference venue part with a map.\\n\\nOutput Format: .ppt file\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Create the base HTML template for the conference website, including DOCTYPE, <head> with meta tags, linked CSS file reference, and placeholder <div> containers for header, navigation, and content sections.\\n  Result: ```html\\n<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html lang=\\\"en\\\">\\n<head>\\n    <meta charset=\\\"UTF-8\\\">\\n    <meta name=\\\"viewport\\\" content=\\\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\\\">\\n    <title>ICLR 2025 - International Conference on Learning Representations</title>\\n    <link rel=\\\"stylesheet\\\" href=\\\"style.css\\\">\\n</head>\\n<body>\\n\\n    <div id=\\\"header\\\">\\n        <!-- Header Content -->\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <div id=\\\"navigation\\\">\\n        <!-- Navigation Menu -->\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <div id=\\\"content\\\">\\n        <!-- Main Content -->\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <div id=\\\"footer\\\">\\n        <!-- Footer Content -->\\n    </div>\\n\\n</body>\\n</html>\\n```\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Develop the CSS stylesheet defining typography, layout grid, header/nav styling, section containers, table styles for schedule, and map container styling.\\n  Result: ```css\\n/* General Styles */\\nbody {\\n    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;\\n    line-height: 1.6;\\n    margin: 0;\\n    padding: 0;\\n    background-color: #f4f4f4;\\n    color: #333;\\n}\\n\\n.container {\\n    width: 80%;\\n    margin: auto;\\n    overflow: hidden;\\n    padding: 0 20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* Typography */\\nh1, h2, h3 {\\n    color: #333;\\n    margin-bottom: 15px;\\n}\\n\\nh1 {\\n    font-size: 2.5em;\\n}\\n\\nh2 {\\n    font-size: 2em;\\n}\\n\\nh3 {\\n    font-size: 1.6em;\\n}\\n\\np {\\n    font-size: 1.1em;\\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* Layout Grid */\\n.grid-2 {\\n    display: grid;\\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\\n    grid-gap: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n.grid-3 {\\n    display: grid;\\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;\\n    grid-gap: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* Header and Navigation */\\nheader {\\n    background: #333;\\n    color: #fff;\\n    padding-top: 30px;\\n    min-height: 70px;\\n    border-bottom: #e8491d 3px solid;\\n}\\n\\nheader a {\\n    color: #fff;\\n    text-decoration: none;\\n    text-transform: uppercase;\\n    font-size: 16px;\\n}\\n\\nheader ul {\\n    margin: 0;\\n    padding: 0;\\n}\\n\\nheader li {\\n    float: left;\\n    display: inline;\\n    padding: 0 20px 0 20px;\\n}\\n\\nheader #branding {\\n    float: left;\\n}\\n\\nheader #branding h1 {\\n    margin: 0;\\n}\\n\\nheader nav {\\n    float: right;\\n    margin-top: 10px;\\n}\\n\\nheader .highlight, header .current a {\\n    color: #e8491d;\\n    font-weight: bold;\\n}\\n\\nheader a:hover {\\n    color: #ccc;\\n    font-weight: bold;\\n}\\n\\n/* Section Containers */\\nsection {\\n    padding: 20px 0;\\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* Schedule Table Styles */\\n.schedule-table {\\n    width: 100%;\\n    border-collapse: collapse;\\n    margin-top: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n.schedule-table th, .schedule-table td {\\n    border: 1px solid #ddd;\\n    padding: 8px;\\n    text-align: left;\\n}\\n\\n.schedule-table th {\\n    background-color: #f2f2f2;\\n    font-weight: bold;\\n}\\n\\n.schedule-table tr:nth-child(even) {\\n    background-color: #f9f9f9;\\n}\\n\\n/* Map Container Styling */\\n.map-container {\\n    position: relative;\\n    padding-bottom: 56.25%; /* 16:9 aspect ratio for map */\\n    height: 0;\\n    overflow: hidden;\\n    margin-top: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n.map-container iframe {\\n    position: absolute;\\n    top: 0;\\n    left: 0;\\n    width: 100%;\\n    height: 100%;\\n}\\n\\n/* Footer */\\nfooter {\\n    background: #333;\\n    color: #fff;\\n    text-align: center;\\n    padding: 20px;\\n    margin-top: 20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* Responsive Design */\\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\\n    .container {\\n        width: 90%;\\n    }\\n\\n    header #branding,\\n    header nav {\\n        float: none;\\n        text-align: center;\\n    }\\n\\n    header h1 {\\n        margin-bottom: 10px;\\n    }\\n\\n    header ul {\\n        padding: 0;\\n    }\\n\\n    header li {\\n        float: none;\\n        display: block;\\n        text-align: center;\\n    }\\n\\n    .grid-2, .grid-3 {\\n        grid-template-columns: 1fr;\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Assemble a .ppt slide deck: one slide per section (Home, Schedule, Venue), embedding the generated HTML snippets and linked CSS content into appropriately formatted slides.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate the Venue section HTML: include venue address (San Francisco, CA, USA) and embed a map iframe pointing to the conference location.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nHTML\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```html\\n<section id=\\\"venue\\\"